Document: RemoteTransform2D
Path: godot/classes/class_remotetransform2d.rst
Summary: RemoteTransform2D synchronizes its Transform2D to a remote Node2D-derived node using global or local coordinate systems.

RemoteTransform2D pushes its own Transform2D to another Node2D derived node (called the remote node) in the scene. It can be set to update another node's position, rotation and/or scale. It can use either global or local coordinates. The remote node's transformation is updated in real-time based on the RemoteTransform2D's properties. This allows for networked synchronization or remote control of node positions without direct scene hierarchy dependencies. The component operates by continuously transmitting its transform data to the target node, which applies the received values to its own transformation.
---CHUNK---
